social_posts.post_text: I forgot to share the second #fennelfannypack that I made. This one was an early Birthday gift for @sewcial_misfit 💕
Look how cute this guy is 🥹😍

Happy Holidays! I can finally share the quilt I made for my mom for Christmas this year! ❤️ I used one @gingiber Birdsong charm pack, the coordinating panel, and some @rileyblakedesigns basics for the borders. No pattern. I simply used what I had and threw it together and made it all fit. It was the only quilt I’ve ever done that for to this extent. No plan, just making things that make me happy. 
.
.
The label is from @sweetwaterfabric and backing is a fabulous @shannonfabrics minky with metallic accents 😍
.
.

Christmas quilt No. 2 was a collaboration between myself and @sewcial_misfit for a friend’s special lady. He wanted a Meadowland with black and white fabrics. We shared the quilt making duties to make it in record time and get it done for him. 
.
.
Fabrics are @modafabrics Create + Grunge and it has charcoal minky for backing. This is your sign to make a B&W Meadowland (pattern by @thencamejune) 
.
.

Happy New Year! I’m going to be ambitious this year and do a temperature quilt 😬 I have already picked my fabric (@rileyblakedesigns Confetti Cottons), printed and cut out 2” x 4” flying geese FPP blocks, and made my first block for today! 
.
.
I chose to do increments of 10 degrees instead of 5 like some people do to keep it a little more simple. I’ll be recording the high and low for each day and making a flying geese unit. 
.
.
Is anyone else doing a temperate quilt? I can’t wait to see how this one turns out! 🌈 
.
.

Believe it or not I have been working on quite a few things the past few weeks. There is another charity quilt in the works, a charity project that’s not a quilt lol, and I started this amazing Kaffe starburst quilt. (Pattern is from the Fat Quarter Workshop book). 

I decided this year would be the year I use hoarded fabric to make something I love. They do me no good on a shelf or in a tote. As much as I fear cutting them up, I don’t want them to never be used. That’s not why I bought them. So this year I will make the things I have been dying to make! 
.
.

I had the pleasure of helping make this beautiful quilt for a local mom who unexpectedly lost her young son recently. Members of the @pcsewcialclub came together to make blocks and complete this quilt to be donated. It was handed off today and we know it will be treasured for a very long time. 
.
.
Our group is dedicated to giving back to the communities we come from and we often do charity work throughout the year, or when the need arises for a heartfelt gift, like this one. Many hands make light work. 🧡
.
.
Heart block tutorial by @cluckclucksew. Long arm quilted by @sewcial_misfit 
.
.

There has not been much sewing going on here aside from working on period pouches for a charity project. I did start an amazing Kaffe quilt that is still in progress, but not much else. I am ready for Spring 
.
.
Picture of Gus just because he’s cute… and getting large. #bassador #bassadorsofinstagram #quiltersofinstagram

I’m alive! And I have finished something! 😂 This cool toned finishing themed quilt was given to my daughters boyfriend this past weekend when he visited us. It’s a pretty mix of prints from my stash with a Cactus Green @shannonfabrics 90” wide solid cuddle on the back. Very cozy!
.
. 
I have sewn here & there throughout the first part of this year but not much. I’ve got 2 quilt tops in progress as well as a raffle quilt for our guild and a charity sewing project (non-quilt related). Believe it or not I’ve seen more at friends houses, or when traveling for sew days and events than I have at my own home. I just needed a break!
.
.
In other news we have 2 full incubators and a brooder full of happy chicks this spring. We’re adding to our flock, so that is always fun! 
.
.

Next project is in the works! This one will be for me. My first ever @heatherbailey quilt. Pattern is #meadowlandquilt 🐝

I have been whipping up scrunchies as fast as I can this week to sell at the @pcsewcialclub Consignment & Bake Sale this weekend 😍 Most of these are Heather Bailey fabric and yes I want to keep them all 😂

I made a new crossbody bag this past week and finished it up yesterday! I modified the #makingbackpack pattern (mini version with alternate pocket option) to include a crossbody strap. This was my first time working with dry oilskin cotton and it is soooo nice!

I haven’t sewn much lately, but I did get this charity quilt done pretty fast! Our dog shelter here in Perry County, OH I struggling and our local government isn’t doing anything to help. The community is coming together to try to raise money for things like A/C repair, building repairs, and more. The dog warden and her staff are sometimes working in 100+ degree temperatures with NO air conditioning inside the building for them or the animals. Some of the walls are literally crumbling. There are so many problems and yet the commissioner won’t fork up any money to help the shelter that serves an entire county in our state. It is pitiful. There is a FB group titled Save The Perry County Dog Shelter where you can find more info. 
.
I will be selling $5.00 raffle tickets for this 60” throw quilt (LellaBoutiqe fabric and Moda Fireside backing) very soon. I’m also willing to ship it anywhere in the continental US if you buy tickets and win the raffle. 
.
I’ll make another post very soon with ways to purchase. My goal is to raise $5,000. I think we can get there! 🧡
.
.

Tickets are available! ⭐️ PLEASE SHARE! I am trying to raise money to save our local dog shelter and rescue center. (more details in my previous post). 🎟️ Tickets are $5.00 each and I’ll ship to the winner anywhere in the continental US if you win! SWIPE for my Venmo code - please add a 🎟️ emoji and your Instagram handle when sending payment. .
.

I realized I forgot to share the second quilt @sewcial_misfit and I have made for the Dolly Parton Imagination Library Fundrasier here in Perry County. The @rubystarsociety / @wattsalot Reading Nook like was literally perfect for this quilt. It was auctioned off last month to raise money for the kids in the county to participate in the Imagination Library from ages 0-5. Such a great program and we are always happy to help! 💜
